  "text": "Larger misalignment was seen for the spinous process region of the semi-automatic method of MR segmentation than the manual segmentation method. This reflects the errors seen around this region from using the segmentation algorithm to define the bone (principally because of partial volume effects). [CITATION_1] reported larger errors when using surface registration points around the spinous process for CT images and postulated that these errors were due to partial volume effects as this structure is so thin. The data in this study also show the largest registration inaccuracy around the spinous process for the CT images.",
